post_text:
Don't forget! The St. Cloud Police Department is hosting a school supply drive to benefit St. Cloud Area School District 742 students for the upcoming school year. Donations are being accepted at the St. Cloud Rotary Community Outpost, 101 11th Avenue North, St. Cloud. Curbside drop-off from 9-11 a.m. Monday, Aug. 31. The Community OutPost team collaborates with residents, community groups, businesses, and St. Cloud State University, to assess community needs; build and maintain relationships; and improve access to needed health, wellness, and other services. Gold Cross Ambulance, CentraCare Health, and Stearns County Social Services have designated space in the facility.

Donations will be delivered to the District Administration Office in Waite Park on August 31st.

It's Apollo school photos tomorrow, Aug. 20, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m.! Get your photo taken while you pick up your device. For efficiency and convenience, you can order your scholar's school pictures online. We ask that all students get their picture taken even if they are not ordering photos. This picture will be used for their school ID and yearbook photo. Student IDs will be required for touchless lunch payment this school year. To pre-order photos: http://my.lifetouch.com/mylifetouch/pictureDayId/EVTHXKRXQ. Students will be allowed to remove their masks for school pictures only.

***Alternative dates for school pictures:
Monday, September 28 (during school day) OR Tuesday, September 29 (during school day)

Reminder! Starting today, Aug.10, both Tech and Apollo will be open for registration for the approved fall sports. Hours will be from 8 - 11 a.m. and 2 - 3:30 p.m. on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday. On Thursday, Aug. 13, the offices will be open from 1 - 6 p.m.

For your convenience, registration packets can be found online on both Tech and Apollo’s activities pages.

Please print these, fill them out and bring them to whichever school your student will be attending this year. If you are in junior high and in a 7 – 12 program, you will need to bring your registration to the high school for processing. If you are a North or Kennedy student, you would go to Apollo; if you are a South student you would go to Tech. Registration fees are $115 and $30 for free/reduced lunch.

post_text:
We couldn't resist sharing this story from one of our Westwood Elementary School families!

"Quincy and Holly drove past her school and they noticed that they were working on (Quincy’s) school. Tonight when I was saying goodnight to her, she asked why they worked on the school every summer. I said that they do that to keep it awesome.

She replied, 'It’s already awesome.'

To which I replied, 'I know. They want to KEEP it awesome for you.'

She then repeated, 'Dad it’s Westwood, It IS awesome.'

So, I again told her they work on it to keep it awesome. She seemed to understand.

I thought it was so cute how much pride she has in her school. Hearing her say she thinks her school is awesome brought tears to my eyes.
That kid probably misses her school more than anyone else I can think of. I’m so happy she loves her school and I’m happy we’ve been a Westwood Family. She’s right, it IS awesome!"

Today is the last day to apply for Pandemic EBT through the State of Minnesota. This program, called P-EBT, is for students who are normally able to get free or reduced price school meals. Apply and get up to $325 per child to spend on groceries. By applying you may also qualify for $100 Summer P-EBT benefits. You do not need to reapply for children you have already submitted an application for.

post_text: Local Education & Activities Foundation (LEAF) wanted to let everyone know that they were able to reach 857 children this week on their 4 book routes. All of the children, parents and even grandparents were so excited and thankful for the opportunity to receive some new books and a bag with math activities. It was a huge success and they want to thank all staff who volunteered to help: Sara Martini, Kirsten Bechtold, Dawn Schoborg, Shelley Rolfes, Andrea Telega, Amy Jensen, Beth Lovdahl and Melissa Hanzsek-Brill. In addition, District 742 Transportation Supervisor Carrie Johnson, who is always so supportive and their wonderful driver, Christopher. And of course, a huge thank you to LEAF and Bruce Hentges for being instrumental in helping to make this happen for all students! It was a fantastic week!

post_text:
A Letter to 2020 Senior Families from Superintendent Jett.
Dear Class of 2020 and Families,

I hope the summer is treating you well, and you enjoyed the unique graduation celebrations last month. As you know, we had hoped to gather the entire Class of 2020 together one last time in July. Regretfully, we will be unable to do so because CDC and MDH guidelines prohibit gatherings of over 250 people for the foreseeable future.

We wish you a safe, healthy summer and extend our sincere well-wishes as you take the next step in your journey. Know that we will always hold you close in our hearts and in our memories as one of the most remarkable, resilient graduating classes.

With highest regards,
Superintendent Jett
text:
A Letter to 2020 Senior Families from Superintendent Jett.
Dear Class of 2020 and Families,

I hope the summer is treating you well, and you enjoyed the unique graduation celebrations last month. As you know, we had hoped to gather the entire Class of 2020 together one last time in July. Regretfully, we will be unable to do so because CDC and MDH guidelines prohibit gatherings of over 250 people for the foreseeable future.

We wish you a safe, healthy summer and extend our sincere well-wishes as you take the next step in your journey. Know that we will always hold you close in our hearts and in our memories as one of the most remarkable, resilient graduating classes.

With highest regards,
Superintendent Jett

post_text:
Anna Roggeman, Tech class of 2020, received a PEO STAR Scholarship!

“The P.E.O. sisterhood is one of the largest community-based women’s organizations in North America. The P.E.O. STAR scholarship recognizes the accomplishments of graduating high school young women planning to pursue post-secondary education. In presenting this $2,500 scholarship, the members of chapter BG are pleased to recognize Anna, who demonstrates excellence in leadership, extra-curricular activities, community service, academics and potential for success.”

post_text: We are PBISProud and 742PROUD!
shared_text:
Minnesota Department of Education
June 10 at 12:38 PM ·

We’re proud to recognize 67 schools and six school districts for their successful work using Positive Behavioral Intervention and Supports (PBIS), a data-driven program that provides schools and districts with training and support to promote positive student behavior, especially for students facing challenges inside and outside of the classroom. Through evidence-based practices, this national program aims to make schools more responsive to the cultures and communities they serve. One important area of focus for the program is on decreasing disparities in discipline, which have historically had negative impacts on educational outcomes for students of color, American Indian students and students with disabilities. The schools receiving recognition are leaders in supporting positive behavior, improving school climate and increasing student achievement. Read more: https://content.govdelivery.com/accounts/MNMDE/bulletins/28fec15

post_text:
IMPORTANT SENIOR FAMILIES UPDATE: On Thursday, May 28 for Tech, and Friday, May 29 for Apollo, we invite you to participate in your school's celebratory parade. Based on today's conversation with the St. Cloud Police Department, and in effort to assist in managing traffic flow, please do your best to attend during the following times:

4:30-5:00 Last names A-F

5:00-5:30 Last names G-L

5:30-6:00 Last names M-R

6:00-6:30 Last names S-Z

To keep everyone safe and healthy, please ensure a family member (not the graduating senior) is driving the vehicle and remain in your vehicle at all times. Graduating seniors and their immediate households must arrive in the same vehicle. KCLD is live-streaming the graduation ceremony so other family members can tune in to 104.7 to listen to the event.

We look forward to seeing you soon.

post_text: A digital slideshow tribute to our seniors will play on billboards each graduation day from 8 a.m. - 6 p.m. to honor the Class of 2020 and their hard work. The billboards are located at 33rd and Division and across from Crossroads Mall by Best Buy. Tech seniors will be celebrated all day May 28 and Apollo seniors will be celebrated all day May 29. Please note that the rotation of slides for the entire senior class will take approximately 40 minutes. Students are organized alphabetically by FIRST NAME. We caution everyone to be aware when driving and not stop or try to park on Division Street. Thanks to Lamar Advertising for making this tribute possible.

post_text: A digital slideshow tribute to our seniors will play on billboards each graduation day from 8 a.m. - 6 p.m. to honor the Class of 2020 and their hard work. The billboards are located at 33rd and Division and across from Crossroads Mall by Best Buy. Tech seniors will be celebrated all day May 28 and Apollo seniors will be celebrated all day May 29. Please note that the rotation of slides for the entire senior class will take approximately 40 minutes. Students are organized alphabetically by FIRST NAME. We caution everyone to be aware when driving and not stop or try to park on Division Street.

post_text: Calling all elementary families! Many students have items remaining in their desks and lockers. Our staff will bag students’ belongings and have them ready for pick up on May 7 from 12-8 p.m. or May 8 from 8 a.m. - 4 p.m. For families choosing to pick up their child’s items from the school, please place a sign in your vehicle window that clearly identifies your child’s first and last name including grade and drive up to the main door. A staff member will bring your child’s items to you. For the health and safety of both you and our staff, please remain in your vehicle. Kennedy families, your time is scheduled for next week Monday, May 11 and Tuesday, May 12 during the secondary pick-up times.
